<ns0:entry xmlns:ns0="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:ns1="http://schemas.google.com/g/2005" xmlns:ns2="http://schemas.google.com/projecthosting/issues/2009" ns1:etag="W/&quot;CkcDQX47eCl7ImA9WhZREk0.&quot;">
		<ns0:id>http://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/full/1610</ns0:id><ns0:author>
			<ns0:name>b...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/105821748722532785568/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">while looking at using sel_universal to create a test for reverse RPC channels, i noticed that sel_universal segfaults if NACLVERBOSITY=4 is used.  it appears to be timing related and doesn't seem to happen when verbosity is low.

tracking this down, i found that DescWrapper in sel_ldr_launcher was used with scoped_ptr, and the command and untrusted wrapped descs were passed into NaClSrpcClientCtor which takes ownership of the reference counts to the descs.  this results in NaClDescUnref eventually getting called twice instead of once for the command channel and untrusted channel descriptors -- once when exiting OpenSrpcChannels, and once again when the channels are dtor'd.

sel_universal relied on this faulting behavior, because it doesn't try to shut down sel_ldr and the waitpid in the sel_ldr_launcher would block.

this could also manifest as surf-away issues.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2011-04-07T18:14:30.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-04-06T05:47:56.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Fixed</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
			<ns2:uri>/u/105821748722532785568/</ns2:uri><ns2:username>b...@google.com</ns2:username></ns2:owner><ns2:state>closed</ns2:state><ns0:title>sel_ldr_launcher did not handle reference counts properly</ns0:title><ns2:label>Type-Defect</ns2:label><ns2:label>Pri-2</ns2:label><ns2:label>Component-TCB</ns2:label><ns2:label>OS-All</ns2:label><ns2:label>Arch-All</ns2:label><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/1610/comments/full" rel="replies" type="application/atom+xml" /><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=1610" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/full/1610" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /><ns2:stars>1</ns2:stars><ns2:closedDate>2011-04-07T18:14:30.000Z</ns2:closedDate><ns2:id>1610</ns2:id></ns0:entry>